Harrison User stories:
-James is a user, he wants to view a selected person’s profile details so that I can understand who they are and see their personal information in one place. 
When he navigates to a user detail page, the application should retrieve the selected user’s information from the backend using the /user/:id endpoint. 
The page should present the information in a readable layout so I can quickly scan the user’s identity and background.

-Jerry wants to move directly from a person’s profile to their photo collection so that they can continue exploring related information without needing to search for it separately.
The user detail page should include an obvious control, such as a button or link, that takes Jerry to the selected user’s photos. This navigation should preserve context by using the same user’s ID in the route.

-Lisa wants the TopBar to show the name of the user whose profile she is viewing so that she always know which record she's currently looking at.
The TopBar should provide page context. On the user detail screen, it should dynamically update to reflect the selected user’s name. 
This helps orient the user and makes the interface feel connected to the current page content.
